    "title": "Brief Alcohol Withdrawal Scale (BAWS)",
    "desc": "The Brief Alcohol Withdrawal Scale (BAWS) assesses alcohol withdrawal symptoms.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28699845/",
                "text": "Rastegar DA, Applewhite D, Alvanzo AAH, Welsh C, Niessen T, Chen ES. Development and implementation of an alcohol withdrawal protocol using a 5-item scale, the Brief Alcohol Withdrawal Scale (Baws). Subst Abus. 2017;38(4):394-400."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p>The BAWS Score is calculated by the addition of the selected points:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 812.149px; border-width: 1px; border-style: none;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 34.7969px;\">\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 78.7234%; height: 34.7969px;\"><strong>Variable</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 34.7969px;\"><strong>Points</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 169.188px; width: 36.4066%;\" rowspan=\"4\">Tremor</td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 34.7969px;\">No tremor</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 34.7969px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 44.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 44.7969px;\">Not visible, but can be felt</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 44.7969px;\">1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 44.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 44.7969px;\">Moderate, with arms extended</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 44.7969px;\">2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 44.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 44.7969px;\">At rest, without arms extended</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 44.7969px;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22.3984px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 134.391px; width: 36.4066%;\" rowspan=\"4\">Diaphoresis/sweats</td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 22.3984px;\">No sweats</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 22.3984px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 44.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 44.7969px;\">Mild, barely visible</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 44.7969px;\">1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22.3984px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 22.3984px;\">Beads of sweat</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 22.3984px;\">2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 44.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 44.7969px;\">Drenching sweats</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 44.7969px;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 44.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 268.781px; width: 36.4066%;\" rowspan=\"4\">Agitation</td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 44.7969px;\">Alert and calm (<calculator id=\"1872\">RASS</calculator> = 0)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 44.7969px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 89.5938px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 89.5938px;\">Restless, anxious, apprehensive, movements not aggressive (RASS = 1)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 89.5938px;\">1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 67.1953px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 67.1953px;\">Agitated, frequent non-purposeful movement (RASS = 2)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 67.1953px;\">2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 67.1953px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 67.1953px;\">Very agitated or combative, violent (RASS = 3 or 4)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 67.1953px;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 52.7656px;\">\n<td rowspan=\"4\" style=\"width: 36.4066%; height: 160.195px;\">Confusion<br><br>e.g. time: by more than 2 days, wrong month, or wrong year<br><br>place:&nbsp;name of building, city, state</td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 52.7656px;\">Oriented to person, place, time</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 52.7656px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 52.7656px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 52.7656px;\">Disoriented to time or place, but not both</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 52.7656px;\">1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 27.3203px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 27.3203px;\">Disoriented to time and place</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 27.3203px;\">2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 27.3438px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 27.3438px;\">Disoriented to person</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 27.3438px;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22.3984px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 22.3984px; width: 36.4066%;\" rowspan=\"4\">Hallucinations (visual, auditory, tactile)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 22.3984px;\">None</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 22.3984px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%;\">Mild (vague report, reality testing intact)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%;\">1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%;\">Moderate (more defined hallucinations)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%;\">2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22.3984px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 42.3168%; height: 22.3984px;\">Severe (obviously responding to internal stimuli, poor reality testing)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2766%; height: 22.3984px;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p></p>",
        "facts": "<p><strong>BAWS &lt;3:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Give diazepam 5 mg orally as needed for mild withdrawal or anxiety.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Every 4 hrs up to 6 doses (day 1).</li>\n<li>Every 6 hrs up to 4 doses (day 2).</li>\n<li>Every 8 hrs up to 3 doses (day 3).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Reassess BAWS every 4 hrs for 24 hrs, then every 6 hrs.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>BAWS 3-5:</strong></p>\n<p>Give diazepam 10 mg orally every 4 hrs until BAWS &lt;3 (up to 10 doses).</p>\n<p>Reassess BAWS every 4 hrs.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>BAWS 6-8:</strong></p>\n<p>Give diazepam 20 mg orally every 2 hrs until BAWS &lt;6 (up to 3 doses).</p>\n<p>If the patient has not received any benzodiazepines, give an initial dose of 10 mg.</p>\n<p>Reassess BAWS every 2 hrs; notify physician if BAWS &gt;5 after 6hrs.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>BAWS &gt;8:</strong></p>\n<p>Give diazepam 20 mg orally and notify physician.</p>",
